    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-05-05T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-05T13:00:00-05:00" n="781"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d781">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.014/89: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-05T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 5, 1943—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:27 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>824. For immediate attention of Under Secretary. The Associated Press carries
                    story taken from pro-Nazi Paris radio that American forces have taken possession
                    of Easter Island and <hi rend="italic">La Opinion</hi> and the Communist paper
                    print the despatch. The Minister of Defense<note n="55" xml:id="d781fn55"
                        >Alfredo Duhalde.</note> has issued a denial. There is no doubt that should
                    we want and need the Island, Chilean Government would agree but Whiting’s
                    inspection showing insufficient drinking water on Island is not favorable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
